column2: VARDESC
Ocular (either eye, by clinical assessment)  Any cataract ever
Ocular (either eye, by clinical assessment)  Retinal change or optic atrophy
Neuropsychiatric Cognitive impairment (e.g., memory deficit, difficulty with calculation, poor concentration, difficulty in spoken or written language, impaired performance level) or major psychosis
Neuropsychiatric Seizures requiring therapy for 6 months
Neuropsychiatric Cerebrovascular accident ever (score 2 if > 1)
Neuropsychiatric Cranial or peripheral neuropathy (excluding optic)
Neuropsychiatric Transverse myelitis
Renal Estimated or measured glomerular filtration rate <50%
Renal Proteinuria > = 3.5 gm/24 hours
Renal End-stage renal disease (regardless of dialysis or transplantation)
Pulmonary Pulmonary hypertension (right ventricular prominence, or loud P2)
Pulmonary Pulmonary fibrosis (physical and radiograph)
Pulmonary Shrinking lung (radiograph)
Pulmonary Pleural fibrosis (radiograph)
Pulmonary Pulmonary infarction (radiograph)
Cardiovascular Angina or coronary artery bypass
Cardiovascular Myocardial infarction ever (score 2 if >I)
Cardiovascular Cardiomyopathy (ventricular dysfunction)
Cardiovascular Valvular disease (diastolic, murmur, or systolic murmur >3/6)
Cardiovascular Pericarditis for 6 months, or pericardiectomy
Peripheral vascular  Claudication for 6 months
Peripheral vascular  Minor tissue loss (pulp space)
Peripheral vascular  Significant tissue loss ever (e.g., loss of digit or limb) (score 2 if >1 site)
Peripheral vascular  Venous thrombosis with swelling, ulceration, or venous stasis
Gastrointestinal Infarction or resection of bowel below duodenum, spleen, liver, or gall bladder ever, for cause any (score 2 if > 1)
Gastrointestinal Mesenteric insufficiency
Gastrointestinal Chronic peritonitis
Gastrointestinal Stricture or upper gastrointestinal tract surgery ever
Musculoskeletal Muscle atrophy or weakness
Musculoskeletal Deforming or erosive arthritis (including reducible deformities, excluding avascular necrosis)
Musculoskeletal Osteoporosis with fracture or vertebral collapse (excluding avascular necrosis)
Musculoskeletal Avascular necrosis (score 2 if > 1 )
Musculoskeletal Osteomyelitis
Skin Scarring chronic alopecia
Skin Extensive scarring or panniculum other than scalp and pulp space
Skin Skin ulceration (excluding thrombosis) for >6 months
Premature gonadal failure
Diabetes (regardless of treatment)
Malignancy (exclude dysplasia) (score 2 if > 1 site)
